name: IL Attorney General
tweet: While buy-now-pay-later loans may appear to make payments more manageable, they may also result in debt accumulation.  I led a coalition urging the @CFPB to ensure that buy-now-pay-later lenders are not engaging in practices that trap consumers in a cycle of debt.

name: IL Attorney General
tweet: Thanks for joining me yesterday @DE_DOJ and @ORDOJ! I'm honored to work beside fearless women who actively fight to make our country a better place.  If you were unable to attend our fireside chat yesterday, you can check it out here:  https://t.co/ZxLClzTVi4  https://t.co/WpRxkGhemb

name: IL Attorney General
tweet: I led an amicus brief urging SCOTUS to reverse a lower court's decision that requires the federal government to continue the Migrant Protection Protocols.  This would have devastating effects on individuals seeking asylum in the U.S. from violence in their native countries.  https://t.co/qo1bys6eZ3

name: IL Attorney General
tweet: Ray Tate has pleaded guilty to murder in the shooting of Wayne County sheriff’s deputy Sean Riley.  While nothing will ever make up for the loss to Deputy Sean Riley’s family and loved ones, I hope this guilty plea brings them some degree of justice and aids in their healing.
